The nutritional food market can be segmented based on product type, distribution channel, and end-user. In terms of product types, the market consists of functional foods, fortified foods, dietary supplements, and other specialized products. Functional foods are those that provide additional health benefits beyond basic nutrition, while fortified foods are enriched with added nutrients. Dietary supplements include vitamins, minerals, herbal products, and other substances consumed to supplement the diet. The market is also segmented by distribution channels including supermarkets/hypermarkets, online retail, convenience stores, and others. Finally, end-users of nutritional foods include children, adults, and the elderly, each with specific dietary requirements and preferences.

